{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1PWN97AwX8v2MajgZU6tK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need to provide a comprehensive report. Let me compile the findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: Host Workflow Script Execution\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of the Cloche codebase to understand how host workflows execute scripts. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. Host Workflow Executor Code (internal/host/)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/`\n\nThe host workflow execution is implemented across multiple files:\n\n- **`executor.go`** (236 lines) - Core StepExecutor implementation that:\n  - Implements `engine.StepExecutor` interface to execute individual host workflow steps\n  - Handles three step types: `StepTypeScript`, `StepTypeWorkflow`\n  - For script steps: runs shell commands via `exec.CommandContext` with shell interpretation (`sh -c`)\n  - For workflow steps: dispatches container workflow runs and polls for completion\n  - Manages step output files and environment variable injection\n\n- **`runner.go`** (148 lines) - High-level orchestration runner that:\n  - Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` DSL file from the project directory\n  - Creates output directories at `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n  - Manages the host run lifecycle (persist to store, track start/completion)\n  - Provides `Run()` and `RunWithID()` methods for executing the workflow\n\n- **`loop.go`** (180 lines) - Continuous orchestration loop that:\n  - Manages concurrent host workflow execution with `MaxConcurrent` limit\n  - Implements backoff/polling when no work is available\n  - Counts active host runs to prevent duplicate execution\n  - Provides `Start()` and `Stop()` methods for lifecycle management\n\n### 2. Script Resolution and Execution\n\n**How scripts are currently resolved:**\n\nScripts are **NOT resolved from a central registry**. Instead, they are invoked directly by their path as specified in the host workflow DSL:\n\n```\nstep prepare-prompt {\n  run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Script Execution Flow** (in `executor.go:executeScript()`):\n\n1. Extract the shell command string from `step.Config[\"run\"]`\n2. Create `exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", cmdStr)`\n3. Set working directory to `ProjectDir` (the project root)\n4. Inject environment variables:\n   - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - Project root directory\n   - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - Path where step should write output\n   - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - Path to previous step's output (if available)\n   - Output mappings from wiring (JSON field extractions as env vars)\n5. Capture combined stdout/stderr via `cmd.CombinedOutput()`\n6. Extract result marker (`CLOCHE_RESULT:` prefix) from output\n7. Write cleaned output to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n8. Return result based on exit code and markers\n\n**Environment Variables Injected:**\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` lines 77-94:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=<projectDir>` - Always provided\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT=<path>` - Always provided\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT=<path>` - If previous step output exists\n- Output mapping variables - When wires have `OutputMap` definitions\n\n### 3. Existing Tests for Host Workflow Execution\n\n**Test File:** `/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go` (694 lines)\n\nComprehensive test coverage including:\n\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_Success` - Basic script execution with success\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_Failure` - Script failure handling (exit 1)\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_ResultMarker` - CLOCHE_RESULT marker extraction\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_EnvironmentVars` - Environment variable injection\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_OutputMappings_JSONFields` - JSON field extraction from previous step output\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_OutputMappings_ArrayIndex` - Array indexing in output mappings\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_OutputMappings_MissingSourceOutput` - Error handling\n- `TestExecutor_WorkflowStep_*` - Workflow dispatch tests\n- `TestEngine_HostWorkflow_Linear` - Full workflow integration\n- `TestRunner_PersistsHostRun` - Run persistence to store\n\n**Test File:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go` (95 lines)\n\n- Loop startup/shutdown behavior\n- Concurrent run management\n- Success/failure backoff logic\n\n### 4. Ports/Interfaces Related to Host Workflows\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\nKey interfaces:\n\n- **`RunStore`** (`ports/store.go`) - Persists host runs:\n  - `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n  - `ListRunsByProject()` - Used to count active host runs\n  - `ListChildRuns()` - Manages parent-child relationships\n\n- **`ContainerRuntime`** (`ports/container.go`) - Started container workflows:\n  - `Start()` - Launch container with config\n  - `Wait()` - Block until completion\n  - `CopyFrom()` - Extract results\n  - `Logs()` - Get container logs\n\n**Interface used by executor:**\n\n- **`RunDispatcher`** (defined in `executor.go` line 44-46):\n  ```go\n  type RunDispatcher interface {\n      RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error)\n  }\n  ```\n  - This is implemented by `adaptgrpc.ClocheServer` in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n### 5. Worktree Setup and Usage\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go`\n\nWorktrees are used for **result extraction** (NOT for script execution):\n\n**How it works:**\n\n1. Container workflow completes and produces results\n2. `ExtractResults()` is called (line 13-93):\n   - Creates temporary directory\n   - Copies container workspace via `docker cp` from `/workspace/.` to tmpdir\n   - Creates git worktree: `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>`\n   - Copies tmpdir contents into worktree (excluding .git)\n   - Creates branch `cloche/<runID>` based on `baseSHA`\n   - Commits with descriptive message showing file changes\n   - Cleans up worktree with `git worktree remove --force`\n\n**Worktree lifecycle:**\n- Created at: `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>/`\n- Cleanup via deferred function ensures removal even on error\n- Gitignore entry: `.gitworktrees/` is added by `cloche init`\n\n**Commit Message Generation:**\n\nBuilt from:\n- Title: `cloche run <runID>: <workflowName> (<result>)`\n- Body: File changeset summary (added, modified, deleted, renamed files)\n\n### 6. Path Resolution for `.cloche/scripts/`\n\n**Script Directory Creation** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` lines 167-171):\n\n```go\nfor _, dir := range []string{\n    clocheDir,\n    filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompts\"),\n    filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"overrides\"),\n    filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"scripts\"),  // <-- Created here\n}\n```\n\n**Script File Creation** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` lines 192-193):\n\n```go\n{filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"host.cloche\"), hostWorkflowTemplate, 0644},\n{filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"scripts\", \"prepare-prompt.sh\"), preparePromptScript, 0755},\n```\n\n**Default Script Template** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` lines 125-136):\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Default prompt generator.\n# Writes the task prompt to stdout and to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n\n${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n\necho \"$prompt\"\n[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n```\n\n**Reference in host.cloche** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` line 109):\n\n```\nrun = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n```\n\n**Path Resolution:**\n\nScripts are resolved **relative to the project directory** because:\n- Executor sets `cmd.Dir = e.ProjectDir` (line 76 in `executor.go`)\n- All commands run with this working directory as CWD\n- Script paths in the DSL (e.g., `bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`) resolve relative to project root\n\n### 7. Design Documentation\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n\nKey design points:\n\n- Host workflows execute on the **host machine** (not in containers)\n- Steps receive environment variables for task context\n- Scripts can write output to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` and stdout\n- Result markers (`CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`) control workflow routing\n- Output files at `.cloche/<orchRunID>/output/<step-name>.out` enable data passing\n- JSON output with path expressions enables structured data extraction across steps\n\n### Summary\n\nThe host workflow execution system is a complete implementation of:\n1. **DSL parsing** - Reads `.cloche/host.cloche` with support for `script` and `workflow` step types\n2. **Step execution engine** - Via `internal/engine/Engine` that walks the workflow graph\n3. **Script invocation** - Direct `sh -c` execution with environment variable injection\n4. **Output capture** - To `.cloche/<runID>/output/` directory files\n5. **Result routing** - Via explicit markers or exit codes\n6. **Persistence** - Host runs stored in SQLite via `RunStore` interface\n7. **Result extraction** - Git worktree-based approach for container workflow outputs\n\nAll file paths are absolute paths in the final response:\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Main script executor\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Workflow runner\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go` - Comprehensive tests\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go` - Loop tests\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - Script and workflow templates\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` - Worktree result extraction\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` - Design specification"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a80b0cf080dd22f18 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 80506\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 55479</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86005800-dc4f-4a50-b6ae-f82ea613cda8","uuid":"0161e62e-a1ad-4554-b299-e7b965473f9d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand how host workflows execute scripts. I need to find:\n\n1. The host workflow executor code (in internal/host/)\n2. How scripts are currently resolved and executed\n3. Any existing tests for host workflow execution\n4. The ports/interfaces related to host workflows\n5. How worktrees are set up and used\n6. Any references to \".cloche/scripts/\" path resolution\n\nBe very thorough - look at all files in internal/host/, and any related code in cmd/cloched/, internal/adapters/, internal/domain/, and internal/ports/.","agentId":"a80b0cf080dd22f18","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need to provide a comprehensive report. Let me compile the findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: Host Workflow Script Execution\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of the Cloche codebase to understand how host workflows execute scripts. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. Host Workflow Executor Code (internal/host/)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/`\n\nThe host workflow execution is implemented across multiple files:\n\n- **`executor.go`** (236 lines) - Core StepExecutor implementation that:\n  - Implements `engine.StepExecutor` interface to execute individual host workflow steps\n  - Handles three step types: `StepTypeScript`, `StepTypeWorkflow`\n  - For script steps: runs shell commands via `exec.CommandContext` with shell interpretation (`sh -c`)\n  - For workflow steps: dispatches container workflow runs and polls for completion\n  - Manages step output files and environment variable injection\n\n- **`runner.go`** (148 lines) - High-level orchestration runner that:\n  - Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` DSL file from the project directory\n  - Creates output directories at `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n  - Manages the host run lifecycle (persist to store, track start/completion)\n  - Provides `Run()` and `RunWithID()` methods for executing the workflow\n\n- **`loop.go`** (180 lines) - Continuous orchestration loop that:\n  - Manages concurrent host workflow execution with `MaxConcurrent` limit\n  - Implements backoff/polling when no work is available\n  - Counts active host runs to prevent duplicate execution\n  - Provides `Start()` and `Stop()` methods for lifecycle management\n\n### 2. Script Resolution and Execution\n\n**How scripts are currently resolved:**\n\nScripts are **NOT resolved from a central registry**. Instead, they are invoked directly by their path as specified in the host workflow DSL:\n\n```\nstep prepare-prompt {\n  run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Script Execution Flow** (in `executor.go:executeScript()`):\n\n1. Extract the shell command string from `step.Config[\"run\"]`\n2. Create `exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", cmdStr)`\n3. Set working directory to `ProjectDir` (the project root)\n4. Inject environment variables:\n   - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - Project root directory\n   - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - Path where step should write output\n   - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - Path to previous step's output (if available)\n   - Output mappings from wiring (JSON field extractions as env vars)\n5. Capture combined stdout/stderr via `cmd.CombinedOutput()`\n6. Extract result marker (`CLOCHE_RESULT:` prefix) from output\n7. Write cleaned output to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n8. Return result based on exit code and markers\n\n**Environment Variables Injected:**\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` lines 77-94:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=<projectDir>` - Always provided\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT=<path>` - Always provided\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT=<path>` - If previous step output exists\n- Output mapping variables - When wires have `OutputMap` definitions\n\n### 3. Existing Tests for Host Workflow Execution\n\n**Test File:** `/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go` (694 lines)\n\nComprehensive test coverage including:\n\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_Success` - Basic script execution with success\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_Failure` - Script failure handling (exit 1)\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_ResultMarker` - CLOCHE_RESULT marker extraction\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_EnvironmentVars` - Environment variable injection\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_OutputMappings_JSONFields` - JSON field extraction from previous step output\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_OutputMappings_ArrayIndex` - Array indexing in output mappings\n- `TestExecutor_ScriptStep_OutputMappings_MissingSourceOutput` - Error handling\n- `TestExecutor_WorkflowStep_*` - Workflow dispatch tests\n- `TestEngine_HostWorkflow_Linear` - Full workflow integration\n- `TestRunner_PersistsHostRun` - Run persistence to store\n\n**Test File:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go` (95 lines)\n\n- Loop startup/shutdown behavior\n- Concurrent run management\n- Success/failure backoff logic\n\n### 4. Ports/Interfaces Related to Host Workflows\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\nKey interfaces:\n\n- **`RunStore`** (`ports/store.go`) - Persists host runs:\n  - `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n  - `ListRunsByProject()` - Used to count active host runs\n  - `ListChildRuns()` - Manages parent-child relationships\n\n- **`ContainerRuntime`** (`ports/container.go`) - Started container workflows:\n  - `Start()` - Launch container with config\n  - `Wait()` - Block until completion\n  - `CopyFrom()` - Extract results\n  - `Logs()` - Get container logs\n\n**Interface used by executor:**\n\n- **`RunDispatcher`** (defined in `executor.go` line 44-46):\n  ```go\n  type RunDispatcher interface {\n      RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error)\n  }\n  ```\n  - This is implemented by `adaptgrpc.ClocheServer` in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n### 5. Worktree Setup and Usage\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go`\n\nWorktrees are used for **result extraction** (NOT for script execution):\n\n**How it works:**\n\n1. Container workflow completes and produces results\n2. `ExtractResults()` is called (line 13-93):\n   - Creates temporary directory\n   - Copies container workspace via `docker cp` from `/workspace/.` to tmpdir\n   - Creates git worktree: `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>`\n   - Copies tmpdir contents into worktree (excluding .git)\n   - Creates branch `cloche/<runID>` based on `baseSHA`\n   - Commits with descriptive message showing file changes\n   - Cleans up worktree with `git worktree remove --force`\n\n**Worktree lifecycle:**\n- Created at: `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>/`\n- Cleanup via deferred function ensures removal even on error\n- Gitignore entry: `.gitworktrees/` is added by `cloche init`\n\n**Commit Message Generation:**\n\nBuilt from:\n- Title: `cloche run <runID>: <workflowName> (<result>)`\n- Body: File changeset summary (added, modified, deleted, renamed files)\n\n### 6. Path Resolution for `.cloche/scripts/`\n\n**Script Directory Creation** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` lines 167-171):\n\n```go\nfor _, dir := range []string{\n    clocheDir,\n    filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompts\"),\n    filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"overrides\"),\n    filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"scripts\"),  // <-- Created here\n}\n```\n\n**Script File Creation** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` lines 192-193):\n\n```go\n{filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"host.cloche\"), hostWorkflowTemplate, 0644},\n{filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"scripts\", \"prepare-prompt.sh\"), preparePromptScript, 0755},\n```\n\n**Default Script Template** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` lines 125-136):\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Default prompt generator.\n# Writes the task prompt to stdout and to $CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nprompt=\"## Task: ${CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE}\n\n${CLOCHE_TASK_BODY}\"\n\necho \"$prompt\"\n[ -n \"${CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT:-}\" ] && echo \"$prompt\" > \"$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT\"\n```\n\n**Reference in host.cloche** (`cmd/cloche/init.go` line 109):\n\n```\nrun = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n```\n\n**Path Resolution:**\n\nScripts are resolved **relative to the project directory** because:\n- Executor sets `cmd.Dir = e.ProjectDir` (line 76 in `executor.go`)\n- All commands run with this working directory as CWD\n- Script paths in the DSL (e.g., `bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`) resolve relative to project root\n\n### 7. Design Documentation\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md`\n\nKey design points:\n\n- Host workflows execute on the **host machine** (not in containers)\n- Steps receive environment variables for task context\n- Scripts can write output to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` and stdout\n- Result markers (`CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`) control workflow routing\n- Output files at `.cloche/<orchRunID>/output/<step-name>.out` enable data passing\n- JSON output with path expressions enables structured data extraction across steps\n\n### Summary\n\nThe host workflow execution system is a complete implementation of:\n1. **DSL parsing** - Reads `.cloche/host.cloche` with support for `script` and `workflow` step types\n2. **Step execution engine** - Via `internal/engine/Engine` that walks the workflow graph\n3. **Script invocation** - Direct `sh -c` execution with environment variable injection\n4. **Output capture** - To `.cloche/<runID>/output/` directory files\n5. **Result routing** - Via explicit markers or exit codes\n6. **Persistence** - Host runs stored in SQLite via `RunStore` interface\n7. **Result extraction** - Git worktree-based approach for container workflow outputs\n\nAll file paths are absolute paths in the final response:\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Main script executor\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Workflow runner\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor_test.go` - Comprehensive tests\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop_test.go` - Loop tests\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - Script and workflow templates\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` - Worktree result extraction\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` - Design specification"}],"totalDurationMs":55479,"totalTokens":80506,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4486,"cache_read_input_tokens":73328,"output_tokens":2685,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4486},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
